    <note>Li(2) Wei(2) [1108] Di's [1096]'s great grandson. During the Jin invasions, the family became scattered with one group moving to Sichuan. The younger sister of Wei(2)'s grandson, Zongzhi(2) [3539], was married to one of Sima(1) Guang's [1488] grandsons and they travelled together to Jiangzhou during the early Southern Song. Zongzhi(2) (q.v.) finally moved to Mingzhou, Yinxian, home of his father-in-law, Xia(2) Cheng [3344] (1106 jinshi). Zongzhi(2)'s eldest daughter married, Jiang(2) Chujun [3226], who was either a son or nephew of Jiang(2) Xin [456]. Since she subsequently married Xia(2) Zuyu [3346], Jiang(2) Chujun must have died at an early age. In 1172-3, Zongzhi(2) was Xingzai zamai wu zamai chang tixian guan and was dismissed as Liangzhe tiju in 1179. XCB, 432.9b, 448.9a, 478.2a, 506.2a, 507.4a, 514.2a; He Yi, Xingzai zamai wu . . ., 2b; Lou Yue, WJ, 101.1a; SHY:ZG, 72.25b-26a.</note>
